-- Philippine bourse says to resume trading at 0535 GMT
-- By Erik dela Cruz
-- Mon May 05, 2014 01:38AM EDT
-- None



MANILA, May 5 (Reuters) - Following an interruption caused by a technical "issues', trading on the Philippine Stock Exchange <.PSI> will resume at 1:35 p.m. (0535 GMT) on Monday and will close at 3:30 p.m. as usual, the bourse said.

Trading was halted at 11:02 a.m..